{
  "texts": [
    "It receives a question, then selects relevant parts in the text and uses them to generate an answer.",
    "We thus have to craft questions carefully (known as prompt engineering -see Lo, 2023) and parse elements of the answer, which can generate additional queries for clarification.",
    "These two aspects are detailed in dedicated subsections below.",
    "When conducting an interview to create a causal map, the interviewer would start with a problem of interest such as obesity or suicide attempt.",
    "In a similar way, the system needs to anchor the causal map in a list of seed terms defined by the user (e.g., 'obesity' and 'overweight')."
  ]
}